# ASTU . BOAP . SEM-II . Course Work repo

## General

### Show help

```sh
markforge --help
```

Show application description, version, author information and command list.

### Show version

```sh
markforge --version
```

Display application version.

---

## Database Commands

### Initialize example database

```sh
markforge db --init
```

```sh
markforge db --init --template <employees|students|patients>
```

Create application database with example schema and demo data.

```sh
markforge db --drop <table_name>
```

```sh
markforge db --list
```

### Initialize custom schema

```sh
markforge db --schema-create \
    --table persons \
    --schema schema.<json|yml|sql>
```

Create user-defined table schema.

### Show schema

```sh
markforge db --schema-show <table_name>
```

Display current database schema.

Reset database

```sh
markforge db reset
```

Delete all tables and recreate the database.

---

## Person / Record Commands

### List records

```sh
markforge data list
```

Show all records.

### View record

```sh
markforge data show --id 1
```

Display a single record.

Add record

```sh
markforge data add
```

Create a new record interactively.

Import record

```sh
markforge data import person.<json|yml|sql>
```

Import records from file.

Update record

```sh
markforge data update --id 1
```

Modify record fields.

Delete record

```sh
markforge data delete --id 1
```

Remove record.

---

Template Commands

List templates

```sh
markforge template list
```

Show available templates.

Show template

```sh
markforge template show invitation
```

Display template contents.

Add template

```sh
markforge template add /path/to/invitation.docx
```

Register a new template.

Remove template

```sh
markforge template delete invitation
```

Delete template.

---

Document Generation

Generate document

```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template invitation \
    --id 1

Generate document for selected person.

Generate all documents

```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template invitation \
    --all

Generate documents for all records.

Output directory

```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template invitation \
    --id 1 \
    --output ./generated

Specify custom output directory.

---

Supported Template Formats

* TXT
* Markdown (MD)
* DOCX
* XLS
* XLSX

Planned support:

* PDF import
* ODT
* HTML

---

Examples

```sh
markforge db init
```

```sh
markforge data list
```

```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template invitation \
    --id 3
```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template report \
